## Research spine (peer-reviewed — Bishop pull)

| Mechanism | Primary literature | Stable id |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Hebbian association** (“fire together, wire together”) | Hebb, D. O. (1949). *The Organization of Behavior.* Wiley. | Classic text — cite by standard bibliographic record |
| **LTP / synaptic plasticity (cellular)** | Bliss & Lømo (1973). Long-lasting potentiation of synaptic transmission in the dentate area of the anaesthetized rabbit following stimulation of the perforant path. **J. Physiol.** 232(2), 331–356. | [DOI 10.1113/jphysiol.1973.sp010274](https://doi.org/10.1113/jphysiol.1973.sp010274) |
| **Dopamine reward prediction / RPE** | Schultz, Dayan, Montague (1997). A neural substrate of prediction and reward. **Science** 275, 1593–1599. | [DOI 10.1126/science.275.5306.1593](https://doi.org/10.1126/science.275.5306.1593) |
| **TD learning (formal)** | Sutton & Barto (2018). *Reinforcement Learning: An Introduction* (2nd ed.). MIT Press. | ISBN 978-0262039249 |
| **Homeostasis / allostasis** | Sterling & Eyer (1988). Allostasis: a new paradigm to explain arousal pathology. In *Handbook of Life Stress, Cognition and Health.* Wiley. | Handbook chapter — standard cite in behavioral neuroscience |
| **Need / drive reduction (motivation)** | Hull, C. L. (1943). *Principles of Behavior.* Appleton-Century-Crofts. | Historical drive-reduction anchor |
| **Free energy / active inference (intrinsic drive framing)** | Friston (2010). The free-energy principle: a unified brain theory? **Nat. Rev. Neurosci.** 11, 127–138. | [DOI 10.1038/nrn2787](https://doi.org/10.1038/nrn2787) |

**Narrative glue:** SIFTA’s plasticity JSON is **not** a spiking network — it is an **explicit, auditable** slow state on disk, analogous to **allostatic set-points** + **RPE-signed updates**, gated by **metabolic danger** and **coarse circadian phase** from `build_now_state()`.

